<br>
Greetings Ayiar,<br>
My name is GM Jamlamin.  To answer your question, the rule is A guild/group/raid of sufficient force that begins the event/ring keeps the event/ring until one of the following happens: a) They give up. b) The mob despawns c) The event concludes.<br>
<br>
After b or c, if there is a group/guild/raid waiting for the next <br>
spawn, the first group no longer has rights to it(I.E. goes to the end of the line).<br>
<br>
<br>
Per your situation 1 - Guild A keeps AoW till one of the 3 conditions above is met.  Anything else is a Kill Steal.<br>
<br>
Per your situation 2 - Guild A keeps Fennin Ro till one of the 3 <br>
conditions above is met.  Anything else is a Kill Steal.<br>
<br>
Sufficient force is needed simply to START the event.  It is possible for the force to get larger or smaller during the event.<br>
<br>
Starting the event is defined as engaging the mobs necessary to start the event.  Mezzing or Charming the mobs and sitting back waiting is not starting the event.<br>
<br>
Simply put, a guild/raid/group will not make gains off another<br>
guild/raid/groups hard work.<br>
<br>
I hope this helps.  Please note this is subject to change as loopholes are found within it.  <br>
<br>
Thank you for your support of all things EverQuest!<br>
 <br>
Game Master Jamlamin<br>
Vazaelle Server<br>
