If you think about it, this is as it should be.  You guys seem to just want one flat answer to see how many loop holes you can find and try to get some situation by where you can just throw it up in the faces of the GMs that they can't touch you.  It's good that the system is set up dynamically so that the GMs have the power to intervene when something is not as it should be.  <br>
<br>
Rather than worry about the specific wording of a set of rules, try applying some common sense.  If you can't look at a situation and determine what would be considered &quot;playing nice&quot; (it is after all the Play Nice Policy) maybe you should seek the help of a six year old in your community that might be able to help you with the concept.  <br>
<br>
I like loopholes as much as the next guy, but recognize when you are defeated by being told that there deliberately are none. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=492380" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://filebox.vt.edu/users/jomarti8/signature.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=meiren>Meiren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 778<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/12/03 10:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2161.topic&index=293>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Obvious.</span><hr size=1> Game Master Jamlamin says, &quot;Yes we advocate cockblocking with 12 people on Vazaelle.&quot;<br>
